thread.title: Corrections & Amplifications

author: wsjcom
title: Corrections & Amplifications
text:
0 COMMENTS ENLARGE In some editions Monday, a Page One chart showing the number of Chinese yuan per U.S. dollar incorrectly said it was showing the number of dollars per yuan.
A wallaby was incorrectly identified as a kangaroo in a photo caption accompanying a Personal Journal article on Aug. 13 about parents who take extended trips with one child at a time.
The watch brand Breitling was incorrectly spelled Brietling in a Personal Journal article July 29 about what a professional understudy packs to go on tour.
In an Aug. 20 Personal Journal article about social-media etiquette, a caption accompanying two photos of social media apps on a smartphone reversed the identifications. The upper photo showed Instagram; the lower photo showed Twitter . TWTR -2.71 %
